The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Punters Corner - Absolute fancied
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      Absolute fancied 
            SRIMAX                                        
	Bangalore: Irfan Ghatala-trained Sun Absolute, who was an easy winner in her debut run, is looking further improved. The horse is expected to beat her three rivals in the 1,400m Royal Calcutta Turf Club Cup, the main attraction in the eight-event race card, here, on Friday. Suraj Narredu partners the three-year-old filly, by Ikhtyar out of Absolutely.          
	SELECTIONS          
	1.30pm: Atomic Queen 1. Spring Beauty 2. A Game To Remember 3.          
	2pm: Yamas 1. Sun Dawn 2. Airplay 3.          
	2.30pm: Sunstone 1. Adonis 2. Gold Turn 3.          
	3pm: Baton Rouge 1. Six Shooter 2. Appolonaire 3.          
	3.30pm: Cherelle 1. Wild Nexus 2. Gazaki 3.          
	4pm: Sun Absolute 1. Delacroix 2. Unleashed 3.          
	4.30pm: Sunny Gold 1. Captains Lover 2. Bucephalas 3.          
	5pm: Vayuputra 1. Sweet Timer 2. Game Dancer 3.          
	Days Best: Sun Absolute Double: Cherelle amp; Sunny Gold.          
